Plant ontogenesis is divided into several periods, including:
1. Germination - the period of seed development from the moment of sowing to the emergence of the first leaf;
2. Seedling stage - the period from the emergence of the first leaf to the formation of the first true leaves;
3. Vegetative stage - the period from the formation of the first true leaves to the formation of the first flowers;
4. Reproductive stage - the period from the formation of the first flowers to the formation of seeds.

